sequenceDiagram
    participant U1 as User 1
    participant U2 as User 2
    participant U3 as User 3
    participant API as VELO API
    participant DB as Database
    participant Bot as Telegram Bot

    Note over U1,Bot: Waitlist Flow: Practice fully booked

    %% Practice setup
    Note over API: Practice created<br/>max_participants = 2

    %% User 1 books
    U1->>API: POST /bookings (practice_id)
    API->>DB: Check availability
    DB-->>API: current_participants = 0
    API->>DB: INSERT booking (user_1)
    API->>DB: UPDATE practice (current = 1)
    API-->>U1: ✓ Booking confirmed

    %% User 2 books
    U2->>API: POST /bookings (practice_id)
    API->>DB: Check availability
    DB-->>API: current_participants = 1
    API->>DB: INSERT booking (user_2)
    API->>DB: UPDATE practice (current = 2)
    API-->>U2: ✓ Booking confirmed

    Note over DB: Practice FULL (2/2)

    %% User 3 tries to book
    U3->>API: POST /bookings (practice_id)
    API->>DB: Check availability
    DB-->>API: current_participants = 2 (FULL!)
    API-->>U3: ❌ Practice full<br/>Join waitlist?

    %% User 3 joins waitlist
    U3->>API: POST /practices/{id}/waitlist
    API->>DB: INSERT waitlist (user_3, position=1)
    DB-->>API: ✓
    API-->>U3: ✓ Added to waitlist<br/>Position: #1

    Note over DB: waitlist:<br/>• user_3, position=1, status=waiting

    %% User 1 cancels
    U1->>API: DELETE /bookings/{booking_id}

    rect rgb(255, 245, 235)
        Note over API,Bot: Automatic Waitlist Processing

        API->>DB: UPDATE booking_1 (cancelled)
        API->>DB: UPDATE practice (current = 1)
        API->>DB: SELECT first from waitlist
        DB-->>API: user_3 (position=1)

        API->>DB: UPDATE waitlist (status=notified, expires_at=now+30min)
        API->>Bot: Send notification to user_3
        Bot->>U3: 🔔 Spot available!<br/>Confirm within 30 minutes<br/>[Confirm] [Decline]
    end

    Note over U3: User has 30 minutes to respond

    alt User confirms in time
        U3->>API: POST /bookings (from waitlist)
        API->>DB: INSERT booking (user_3)
        API->>DB: UPDATE practice (current = 2)
        API->>DB: UPDATE waitlist (status=converted)
        API-->>U3: ✓ Booking confirmed!

        Note over DB: Practice FULL again (2/2)

    else User declines
        U3->>API: POST /waitlist/{id}/decline
        API->>DB: UPDATE waitlist (status=declined)
        API->>DB: SELECT next from waitlist
        DB-->>API: (no more users)
        API-->>U3: ✓ Removed from waitlist

        Note over DB: Practice has 1 spot open

    else User doesn't respond (30 min timeout)
        Note over Bot: 30 minutes elapsed
        API->>DB: UPDATE waitlist (status=expired)
        API->>DB: SELECT next from waitlist
        DB-->>API: (no more users)
        Bot->>U3: ⏰ Waitlist spot expired

        Note over DB: Practice has 1 spot open
    end

    %% Multiple users on waitlist
    rect rgb(232, 245, 233)
        Note over U1,DB: Scenario: Multiple waitlist users

        Note over DB: Practice: 2/2 spots<br/>Waitlist:<br/>• user_4, position=1<br/>• user_5, position=2<br/>• user_6, position=3

        Note over U2: User 2 cancels

        Note over API,Bot: Process waitlist in order:<br/>1. Notify user_4 (position=1)<br/>2. If user_4 declines/expires → notify user_5<br/>3. If user_5 declines/expires → notify user_6<br/>4. If all decline/expire → spot stays open
    end

    %% Waitlist model
    rect rgb(227, 242, 253)
        Note over DB: Waitlist Table Schema
        Note over DB: • id<br/>• practice_id<br/>• user_id<br/>• position (auto-increment)<br/>• status (waiting|notified|converted|declined|expired)<br/>• joined_at<br/>• notified_at<br/>• expires_at (notified_at + 30 min)<br/>• created_at
    end

    Note over U1,Bot: Waitlist ensures fair access + automatic notifications
